Los Mariachis is my favorite place for authentic Mexican cuisine.  The staff is always very happy to see guests, the decor is bright and cheerful and the food is fresh and delicious! My wife and I usually start with nachos, which are a single layer of carefully arranged tortillas, individually covered with refried beans,  cheese, lettuce, chorizo,tomatoes,  and love.  They are served with a cup of guacamole and some jalapenos.  The meal actually starts with a complimentary bowl of chips, salsa, pico de gallo, radishes, lime wedges, and crema, which is just happiness in a wooden bowl! I've worked the menu quite a bit and never been disappointed.  I love the tacos; the chicken molé is fantastic; the burritos are all winners... Clearly,  I like this place, as does the largely Mexican clientele. On Fridays,  the live Mariachis will entertain you, too! Go by yourself , on a date, or with a group. JUST GO! Delivery is not a bad idea,  either.

After passing by this place for 20 years, I'm mad I didn't go in sooner but at least I got to celebrate my latest birthday in style here.  The mariachi band starts playing around 8, so we came in for dinner around 7, with a reservation. If you want to be sure to sit in the main dining room (the other is sit down but feels more to go), make a reservation.  We had a nice round table in the back which gave us easy access to the (not wheelchair-accessible) bathrooms and a great view of the band.  I tried the Mexican steak and spicy pulled beef; both were so delicious! The guacamole was also really good (similar to what I've had in Mexico) as were the table sauces.  If you're coming for the mariachi band, bring cash to tip them!  Prices are fair, sangria is strong and portions are good.  Loved my experience here!
